cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper is about image classification using a new algorithm called CapsNet, which is a recent development in the field of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also evaluates the performance of CapsNet in comparison with other classifiers, which involves machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses datasets of images, which may also make it relevant to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
